The paper deals with lower bounds for approximating the matching polytope, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve linear programming and the non-negative rank of a matrix, which are common topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of approximating the matching polytope also has connections to graph theory (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), and game theory (cs.GT).
